StringWithMarkup.String: Maleic anhydride appears as colorless crystalline needles, flakes, pellets, rods, briquettes, lumps or a fused mass. Melts at 113°F. Shipped both as a solid and in the molten state. Vapors, fumes and dusts strong irritate the eyes, skin and mucous membranes. Flash point 218°F. Autoignition temperature 890°F. Used to make paints and plastics and other chemicals.
COLOURLESS OR WHITE CRYSTALS WITH PUNGENT ODOUR.
Colorless needles, white lumps, or pellets with an irritating, choking odor.
